comment: I just stumbled upon this whilst on YouTube but it completely resonated with me. I've been happily with my third wife for 12 years and spent a similar time with my first wife who I remain good friends with. In between I was married to an abusive woman for less than two years who of course, drum roll, accused me of being abusive when no one else in my entire life ever did. So when I saw this I felt a real sense of empathy with me Depp's position. I get the me too movement from  philosophical perspective but societally we need to get a handle on evidentiary based information and not just condemn anyone without due process. That goes for the media, social media and the judiciary. When I first heard this story I like others just assumed Johnny Depp had been in the wrong because I never bothered to question it and frankly it wasn't important enough to me to check on sources. It was merely gossip. But it's a massive reminder to anyone to think about the information you receive and question it before blindly accepting it.

comment:
It was very unfair that Johnny was let go from some movie roles, but you have to be realistic: So many people work on a movie and their jobs are dependent on the movie doing well. Box office bombs have brought down entire movie companies, with loss of jobs. You can‚Äôt risk that. Johnny was controversial, and people could then stay away from your movie if he‚Äôs in it. Other actors might want to opt out of the movie because they don‚Äôt want to be associated with him. 
It was sad for Johnny, but you can be sure he‚Äôs doing fine moneywise. It‚Äôs the hundreds of other employees that need to be considered.

A similar situation is when Charlie Sheen was fired from 2.5men, or Roseanne from Roseanne. People were angry that the shows continued. Well, think of those shows as companies with many employees. You don‚Äôt suddenly end an entire company because of one person. But somehow viewers can‚Äôt see past the bunch of actors they see on screen. They see it as pure entertainment, for fun, and cannot imagine that it‚Äôs just like any other company, where your mother might work as a caterer or cleaner to be able to take care of you.
